Document: AudioEffectDelay
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectdelay.rst
Summary: A delay audio effect that can be used to create echoes and other time-based effects.

AudioEffectDelay

Inherits: AudioEffect < AudioEffect
Description: A delay audio effect that can be used to create echoes and other time-based effects.

Properties:
dry (float): The amount of the original signal to mix in. Default: 1.0. Range: 0.0 to 1.0.
feedback (float): The amount of the delayed signal to mix back into the delay buffer. This controls the number of echoes. Default: 0.5. Range: 0.0 to 1.0.
delay_time_ms (float): The delay time in milliseconds. Default: 1000.0. Range: 0.0 to 10000.0.
low_pass (float): The cutoff frequency for the low-pass filter applied to the delayed signal. Default: 1000.0. Range: 20.0 to 20000.0.
mix_wet (float): The amount of the delayed signal to mix in. Default: 0.5. Range: 0.0 to 1.0.
