Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectdelay.rst
Summary: This document describes the AudioEffectDelay class in Godot, which implements a delay audio effect.

Inherits: AudioEffect < AudioEffect
Introduced in: 3.0

AudioEffectDelay
================================================================================

.. rst-class:: classref-introduction

A delay audio effect.

Properties
----------

+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+
| Property                           | Type                               | Description                        |
+====================================+====================================+====================================+
| :ref:`mix`                         | :ref:`float <class_float>`         | The amount of delay effect to mix. |
+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+
| :ref:`feedback`                    | :ref:`float <class_float>`         | The amount of feedback for the delay. |
+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+
| :ref:`delay_time_sec`              | :ref:`float <class_float>`         | The delay time in seconds.         |
+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+
| :ref:`dry`                         | :ref:`float <class_float>`         | The amount of dry signal to mix.   |
+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+
| :ref:`wet`                         | :ref:`float <class_float>`         | The amount of wet signal to mix.   |
+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+------------------------------------+

Properties
----------

mix (float): The amount of delay effect to mix. Default: 1.0.
feedback (float): The amount of feedback for the delay. Default: 0.0.
delay_time_sec (float): The delay time in seconds. Default: 0.0.
dry (float): The amount of dry signal to mix. Default: 1.0.
wet (float): The amount of wet signal to mix. Default: 0.0.
