Document: AudioEffectDelay
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectdelay.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of the AudioEffectDelay class, which controls delay effects in audio processing.

Properties:
* dry (float): The dry signal level. Default: 1.0
* feedback_active (bool): Enables or disables the feedback loop for the delay. Default: false
* feedback_delay_ms (float): The delay time in milliseconds for the feedback loop. Default: 340.0
* feedback_level_db (float): The level in decibels for the feedback signal. Default: -6.0
* feedback_lowpass (float): The cutoff frequency in Hz for the low-pass filter applied to the feedback signal. Default: 16000.0
* tap1_active (bool): Enables or disables the first delay tap. Default: true
* tap1_delay_ms (float): The delay time in milliseconds for the first tap. Default: 250.0
* tap1_level_db (float): The level in decibels for the first tap. Default: -6.0
* tap1_pan (float): The stereo panning for the first tap. Ranges from -1.0 (left) to 1.0 (right). Default: 0.2
* tap2_active (bool): Enables or disables the second delay tap. Default: true
* tap2_delay_ms (float): The delay time in milliseconds for the second tap. Default: 500.0
* tap2_level_db (float): The level in decibels for the second tap. Default: -12.0
* tap2_pan (float): The stereo panning for the second tap. Ranges from -1.0 (left) to 1.0 (right). Default: -0.4
---CHUNK---
Document: AudioEffectDelay
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectdelay.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the AudioEffectDelay class, controlling dry volume, feedback, and two independent delay taps.

Property Descriptions
dry (float): The volume ratio of the original audio. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default: 1.0
  Method: set_dry(value: float)
  Method: get_dry() → float

feedback_active (bool): If true, feedback is enabled, repeating taps after they are played. Default: false
  Method: set_feedback_active(value: bool)
  Method: is_feedback_active() → bool

feedback_delay_ms (float): Feedback delay time in milliseconds. Value can range from 0 to 1500. Default: 340.0
  Method: set_feedback_delay_ms(value: float)
  Method: get_feedback_delay_ms() → float

feedback_level_db (float): Gain for feedback, in dB. Value can range from -60 to 0. Default: -6.0
  Method: set_feedback_level_db(value: float)
  Method: get_feedback_level_db() → float

feedback_lowpass (float): Low-pass filter for feedback, in Hz. Frequencies above this value are filtered out. Value can range from 1 to 16000. Default: 16000.0
  Method: set_feedback_lowpass(value: float)
  Method: get_feedback_lowpass() → float

tap1_active (bool): If true, the first tap will be enabled. Default: true
  Method: set_tap1_active(value: bool)
  Method: is_tap1_active() → bool

tap1_delay_ms (float): First tap delay time in milliseconds, compared to the original audio. Value can range from 0 to 1500. Default: 250.0
  Method: set_tap1_delay_ms(value: float)
  Method: get_tap1_delay_ms() → float

tap1_level_db (float): Gain for the first tap, in dB. Value can range from -60 to 0. Default: -6.0
  Method: set_tap1_level_db(value: float)
  Method: get_tap1_level_db() → float

tap1_pan (float): Pan position for the first tap. Negative values pan the sound to the left, positive pan to the right. Value can range from -1 to 1. Default: 0.2
  Method: set_tap1_pan(value: float)
  Method: get_tap1_pan() → float

tap2_active (bool): If true, the second tap will be enabled. Default: true
  Method: set_tap2_active(value: bool)
  Method: is_tap2_active() → bool

tap2_delay_ms (float): Second tap delay time in milliseconds, compared to the original audio. Value can range from 0 to 1500. Default: 500.0
  Method: set_tap2_delay_ms(value: float)
  Method: get_tap2_delay_ms() → float

tap2_level_db (float): Gain for the second tap, in dB. Value can range from -60 to 0. Default: -12.0
  Method: set_tap2_level_db(value: float)
  Method: get_tap2_level_db() → float

tap2_pan (float): Pan position for the second tap. Negative values pan the sound to the left, positive pan to the right. Value can range from -1 to 1. Default: -0.4
  Method: set_tap2_pan(value: float)
  Method: get_tap2_pan() → float